-- Taser Call Trading Surges, Shares Advance Before Earnings Report Next Week
-- Jeff Kearns
-- 2010-07-21T16:13:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/taser-call-trading-surges-shares-advance-before-earnings-report-next-week.html

          
          
             Trading of bullish  Taser
International Inc . options jumped to the highest in almost two
years as investors boosted wagers that the world’s largest maker
of stun guns will pare this year’s loss after reporting results
next week.  
 More than  12,000 calls to buy the stock changed hands, 38
times the four-week average and 36 times the number of puts to
sell. The shares climbed 8.3 percent to $4.17 at 12:09 p.m. in
New York. Taser has rebounded from an almost 16-month low of
$3.70 on July 1. It peaked in 2010 at $7.63 in February.  
 Taser, based in Scottsdale, Arizona-based, will report a
second-quarter loss of 1 cent a share on July 27, according to
the average of four analyst estimates in a Bloomberg survey.  
